  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively selling into strength as SPX trades right at the max positive gamma strike (6580) with spot just 10 points below the GEX flip at 6590 - they're providing liquidity against the recent momentum spike evidenced by the 6.2% 1-min move. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls at 6575-6590 should cap upside and create mean reversion pressure back toward 6550-6560 as dealers hedge their long gamma positions. Critical level is the 6590 flip - any sustained break above flips dealers to short gamma and removes the stabilizing force, while a rejection here confirms the gamma ceiling and targets a pullback toward the 6500 negative gamma magnet.",
